{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.032Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Attention lets a model "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "dynamically weight",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " which parts of an input sequence matter when producing each output representation. In agentic systems built on LLMs, attention is why a model can relate a user goal stated at the start of a long context to a tool argument generated thousands of tokens later."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Attention maps a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "query",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " vector against a set of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " vectors to produce weights, then forms a weighted sum of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "value",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " vectors. The core formula for scaled dot-product attention is "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\text{Attention}(Q,K,V)=\\text{softmax}\\left(\\frac{QK^\\top}{\\sqrt{d_k}}\\right)V"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "where "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "Q"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "K"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "V"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are matrices built from input embeddings via learned projections "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "W_Q, W_K, W_V"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Each row corresponds to one token position. Softmax turns raw compatibility scores into a probability distribution over positions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before attention, RNNs passed information sequentially; distant tokens interacted only through many hops, causing vanishing influence. Attention creates "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "direct paths",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " between any pair of positions. For agents, that means instructions, retrieved documents, prior tool outputs, and error messages can all interact in one forward pass—critical for multi-step reasoning over long transcripts."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Long-range context",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — any token can attend to any other in one layer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Parallelism",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — attention matrices compute on GPUs without sequential recurrence"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Interpretability",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — weight patterns can be inspected (with caveats) to see what the model emphasizes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Flexible routing",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the same mechanism supports self-attention, cross-attention, and masked causal attention"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Quadratic cost",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — standard attention is "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "inlineMath",
                    "attrs": {
                      "latex": "O(n^2)"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " in sequence length for memory and compute"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No built-in order",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — attention is permutation-equivariant without positional encoding"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Softmax saturation",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — very large dot products can produce near one-hot weights, reducing gradient flow"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Compatibility scores"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For token "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " querying token "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "j"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the score is the dot product "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "q_i \\cdot k_j"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". High scores mean the query finds the key relevant. Scaling by "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\sqrt{d_k}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " keeps dot-product variance stable as dimension grows."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "From scores to output"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After softmax over keys, the output for position "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\sum_j \\alpha_{ij} v_j"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " where "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\alpha_{ij}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are attention weights. Each output vector mixes value vectors according to relevance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Simplified single-head attention (batch dim omitted)\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\n\ndef scaled_dot_product_attention(Q, K, V, mask=None):\n    d_k = Q.size(-1)\n    scores = Q @ K.transpose(-2, -1) / (d_k ** 0.5)\n    if mask is not None:\n        scores = scores.masked_fill(mask == 0, float('-inf'))\n    weights = F.softmax(scores, dim=-1)\n    return weights @ V, weights"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Transformer-based LLMs use attention in every layer. Agent builders rarely implement attention directly, but understanding it explains "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "context limits",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", why very long prompts cost more, and why retrieval-augmented agents benefit from placing key facts where attention can reach them."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comparison with alternatives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RNN hidden state",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — sequential, hard to parallelize, weak long-range links"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Convolution",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — local receptive field unless stacked deeply"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Linear attention variants",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — approximate full attention for long sequences at lower cost"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Treat each token as asking: \"Who in this context should I listen to right now?\" Attention answers by distributing a fixed budget of focus (weights summing to 1) across all candidates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An agent receives a 20k-token transcript: system policy, user task, five retrieved API docs, and three prior tool failures. When generating the next JSON tool call, upper layers assign high attention to the failure messages and the schema snippet—without re-reading the entire history sequentially."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming attention weights always equal human \"importance\" — they are one internal signal among many"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring causal masks in decoder-only models — future tokens must be masked during training and inference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Underestimating memory: doubling context length roughly quadruples attention memory"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Attention computes relevance-weighted mixtures of value vectors using query–key compatibility"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Scaling by "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "inlineMath",
                    "attrs": {
                      "latex": "\\sqrt{d_k}"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " stabilizes softmax inputs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Quadratic sequence cost shapes agent context budgets and retrieval design"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The same mechanism powers self-attention inside blocks and cross-attention in encoder–decoder setups"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
